\n- `--repo-path` — Absolute path to the repository\\n\\n**Output (stdout):** JSON\\n\\n```json\\n{\\\"session_dir\\\": \\\"/path/to/sessions\\\"}\\n```\\n\\n#### `resolve-session-file --session-dir <dir> --session-id <id>`\\n\\nResolves the session file path from a session directory and ID.\\n\\n**Arguments:**\\n- `--session-dir` — Session directory path\\n- `--session-id` — Session identifier\\n\\n**Output (stdout):** JSON\\n\\n```json\\n{\\\"session_file\\\": \\\"/path/to/session/file.jsonl\\\"}\\n```\\n\\n#### `read-session`\\n\\nReads session data from a hook input event.\\n\\n**Input (stdin):** JSON — the HookInput object\\n\\n**Output (stdout):** JSON — AgentSession object\\n\\n```json\\n{\\n  \\\"session_id\\\": \\\"abc123\\\",\\n  \\\"session_file\\\": \\\"/path/to/file.jsonl\\\"\\n}\\n```\\n\\n#### `write-session`\\n\\nWrites/updates session data.\\n\\n**Input (stdin):** JSON — the AgentSession object\\n\\n**Output:** Exit 0 on success.\\n\\n#### `read-transcript --session-ref <path>`\\n\\nReads a transcript file and returns its raw bytes.\\n\\n**Arguments:**\\n- `--session-ref` — Path to the transcript file\\n\\n**Output (stdout):** Raw transcript bytes.\\n\\n#### `chunk-transcript --max-size <n>`\\n\\nSplits a transcript into chunks for storage.\\n\\n**Input (stdin):** Raw transcript bytes.\\n\\n**Arguments:**\\n- `--max-size` — Maximum chunk size in bytes\\n\\n**Output (stdout):** JSON\\n\\n```json\\n{\\\"chunks\\\": [\\\"<base64-encoded-chunk>\\\", \\\"...\\\"]}\\n```\\n\\n#### `reassemble-transcript`\\n\\nReassembles transcript chunks back into a full transcript.\\n\\n**Input (stdin):** JSON\\n\\n```json\\n{\\\"chunks\\\": [\\\"<base64-encoded-chunk>\\\", \\\"...\\\"]}\\n```\\n\\n**Output (stdout):** Raw transcript bytes.\\n\\n#### `format-resume-command --session-id <id>`\\n\\nReturns the command a user can run to resume a session.\\n\\n**Arguments:**\\n- `--session-id` — Session identifier\\n\\n**Output (stdout):** JSON\\n\\n```json\\n{\\\"command\\\": \\\"cursor --resume abc123\\\"}\\n```\\n\\n### Capability: `hooks`\\n\\nThese subcommands are required when `capabilities.hooks` is `true`.\\n\\n#### `parse-hook --hook <name>`\\n\\nParses a raw agent hook payload into a structured event.\\n\\n**Arguments:**\\n- `--hook` — Hook name (e.g., \\\"stop\\\", \\\"session-start\\\")\\n\\n**Input (stdin):** Raw agent hook payload bytes.\\n\\n**Output (stdout):** JSON — the parsed event, or `null` if the payload is not relevant.\\n\\n#### `install-hooks [--local-dev] [--force]`\\n\\nInstalls agent hooks for Entire integration.\\n\\n**Arguments:**\\n- `--local-dev` — Use local development binary path (optional)\\n- `--force` — Overwrite existing hooks (optional)\\n\\n**Output (stdout):** JSON\\n\\n```json\\n{\\\"hooks_installed\\\": 3}\\n```\\n\\n#### `uninstall-hooks`\\n\\nRemoves installed agent hooks.\\n\\n**Arguments:** None\\n\\n**Output:** Exit 0 on success.\\n\\n#### `are-hooks-installed`\\n\\nChecks whether hooks are currently installed.\\n\\n**Arguments:** None\\n\\n**Output (stdout):** JSON\\n\\n```json\\n{\\\"installed\\\": true}\\n```\\n\\n### Capability: `transcript_analyzer`\\n\\nRequired when `capabilities.transcript_analyzer` is `true`.\\n\\n#### `get-transcript-position --path <path>`\\n\\nReturns the current byte position/size of a transcript file.\\n\\n**Arguments:**\\n- `--path` — Path to the transcript file\\n\\n**Output (stdout):** JSON\\n\\n```json\\n{\\\"position\\\": 12345}\\n```\\n\\n#### `extract-modified-files --path <path> --offset <n>`\\n\\nExtracts the list of files modified by the agent from a transcript.\\n\\n**Arguments:**\\n- `--path` — Path to the transcript file\\n- `--offset` — Byte offset to start reading from\\n\\n**Output (stdout):** JSON\\n\\n```json\\n{\\\"files\\\": [\\\"path/to/file1.go\\\", \\\"path/to/file2.go\\\"]}\\n```\\n\\n#### `extract-prompts --session-ref <path> --offset <n>`\\n\\nExtracts user prompts from a transcript.\\n\\n**Arguments:**\\n- `--session-ref` — Path to the transcript file\\n- `--offset` — Byte offset to start reading from\\n\\n**Output (stdout):** JSON\\n\\n```json\\n{\\\"prompts\\\": [\\\"first prompt text\\\", \\\"second prompt text\\\"]}\\n```\\n\\n#### `extract-summary --session-ref <path>`\\n\\nExtracts an AI-generated summary from a transcript.\\n\\n**Arguments:**\\n- `--session-ref` — Path to the transcript file\\n\\n**Output (stdout):** JSON\\n\\n```json\\n{\\\"summary\\\": \\\"Summary text here\\\", \\\"has_summary\\\": true}\\n```\\n\\n### Capability: `transcript_preparer`\\n\\nRequired when `capabilities.transcript_preparer` is `true`.\\n\\n#### `prepare-transcript --session-ref <path>`\\n\\nPrepares/processes a transcript file (e.g., converting from raw format).\\n\\n**Arguments:**\\n- `--session-ref` — Path to the transcript file\\n\\n**Output:** Exit 0 on success.\\n\\n### Capability: `token_calculator`\\n\\nRequired when `capabilities.token_calculator` is `true`.\\n\\n#### `calculate-tokens --offset <n>`\\n\\nCalculates token usage from a transcript.\\n\\n**Input (stdin):** Raw transcript bytes.\\n\\n**Arguments:**\\n- `--offset` — Byte offset to start calculating from\\n\\n**Output (stdout):** JSON\\n\\n```json\\n{\\\"input_tokens\\\": 1500, \\\"output_tokens\\\": 500}\\n```\\n\\n### Capability: `text_generator`\\n\\nRequired when `capabilities.text_generator` is `true`.\\n\\n#### `generate-text --model <model>`\\n\\nGenerates text using the agent's underlying LLM.\\n\\n**Input (stdin):** Prompt text.\\n\\n**Arguments:**\\n- `--model` — Model to use for generation\\n\\n**Output (stdout):** JSON\\n\\n```json\\n{\\\"text\\\": \\\"Generated response text\\\"}\\n```\\n\\n### Capability: `hook_response_writer`\\n\\nRequired when `capabilities.hook_response_writer` is `true`.\\n\\n#### `write-hook-response --message <message>`\\n\\nWrites a message in the agent's native hook response format.\\n\\n**Arguments:**\\n- `--message` — Message to write\\n\\n**Output (stdout):** Agent-native format bytes (e.g., JSONL for Claude Code).\\n\\n### Capability: `subagent_aware_extractor`\\n\\nRequired when `capabilities.subagent_aware_extractor` is `true`.\\n\\n#### `extract-all-modified-files --offset <n> --subagents-dir <dir>`\\n\\nExtracts modified files from both the main transcript and any subagent transcripts.\\n\\n**Input (stdin):** Raw main transcript bytes.\\n\\n**Arguments:**\\n- `--offset` — Byte offset for the main transcript\\n- `--subagents-dir` — Directory containing subagent transcripts\\n\\n**Output (stdout):** JSON\\n\\n```json\\n{\\\"files\\\": [\\\"file1.go\\\", \\\"file2.go\\\"]}\\n```\\n\\n#### `calculate-total-tokens --offset <n> --subagents-dir <dir>`\\n\\nCalculates total token usage across main transcript and subagent transcripts.\\n\\n**Input (stdin):** Raw main transcript bytes.\\n\\n**Arguments:**\\n- `--offset` — Byte offset for the main transcript\\n- `--subagents-dir` — Directory containing subagent transcripts\\n\\n**Output (stdout):** JSON\\n\\n```json\\n{\\\"input_tokens\\\": 5000, \\\"output_tokens\\\": 2000}\\n```\\n\\n## Error Handling\\n\\n- Exit code `0` indicates success.\\n- Any non-zero exit code indicates an error.\\n- Error messages should be written to stderr.\\n- The CLI captures stderr and wraps it in a Go error.\\n- If the binary is not found in PATH, the agent is simply not registered.\\n- If `info` fails or returns invalid JSON, the binary is skipped during discovery.\\n\\n## Versioning\\n\\nThe protocol version is declared in the `info` response (`protocol_version` field) and set via `ENTIRE_PROTOCOL_VERSION` environment variable. The CLI checks that the binary's protocol version matches its expected version before registering the agent.\\n\\nFuture protocol versions may add new subcommands or capabilities. Existing subcommands will maintain backwards compatibility within a major version.\\n\",\"structuredPatch\":[],\"originalFile\":null},\"sourceToolAssistantUUID\":\"725d6173-d6f3-4708-9ad7-8a8aeb8a7590\"}\n{\"type\":\"queue-operation\",\"operation\":\"remove\",\"timestamp\":\"2026-03-04T09:59:15.649Z\",\"sessionId\":\"b12319af-9a0a-4691-b084-e5fc5ae7e446\"}\n{\"type\":\"queue-operation\",\"operation\":\"enqueue\",\"timestamp\":\"2026-03-04T09:59:17.412Z\",\"sessionId\":\"b12319af-9a0a-4691-b084-e5fc5ae7e446\",\"content\":\"<task-notification>\\n<task-id>a43a1642d00468d04</task-id>\\n<tool-use-id>toolu_01UVn2PdSxj7uf2VdusS64SW</tool-use-id>\\n<status>completed</status>\\n<summary>Agent \\\"Explore agent architecture\\\" completed</summary>\\n<result>Now let me create a comprehensive report of my findings:\\n\\n## Comprehensive Agent Architecture Exploration Report\\n\\nI've completed a thorough exploration of the Entire CLI agent architecture, with specific focus on the Cursor agent implementation. Here's my detailed findings:\\n\\n### 1. Agent Interface and Optional Interfaces\\n\\n**Main Agent Interface** (`/Users/nodo/work/cli/cmd/entire/cli/agent/agent.go`):\\n\\nThe `Agent` interface consists of 14 methods organized into three groups:\\n\\n**Identity (5 methods):**\\n- `Name()` - Returns registry key (e.g., \\\"cursor\\\")\\n- `Type()` - Returns agent type identifier (e.g., \\\"Cursor\\\") for metadata/trailers\\n- `Description()` - Human-readable UI description\\n- `IsPreview()` - Whether integration is in preview or stable\\n- `DetectPresence(ctx context.Context)` - Checks if agent is configured in repo\\n- `ProtectedDirs()` - Repo-root-relative directories never to modify/delete\\n\\n**Transcript Storage (3 methods):**\\n- `ReadTranscript(sessionRef string)` - Reads raw transcript bytes\\n- `ChunkTranscript(ctx, content, maxSize)` - Splits transcript if over maxSize (format-aware, handles JSONL line boundaries and JSON message arrays)\\n- `ReassembleTranscript(chunks)` - Combines chunks back together (format-specific)\\n\\n**Legacy Methods (6 methods)** - Will move to optional interfaces in Phase 4:\\n- `GetSessionID(input)` - Extracts session ID from hook input\\n- `GetSessionDir(repoPath)` - Where agent stores session data\\n- `ResolveSessionFile(sessionDir, agentSessionID)` - Path to session transcript file\\n- `ReadSession(input)` - Reads session data from agent's storage\\n- `WriteSession(ctx, session)` - Writes session data for resumption\\n- `FormatResumeCommand(sessionID)` - Command to resume session\\n\\n**Optional Interfaces:**\\n\\n1. **HookSupport** - For agents with lifecycle hooks (Claude Code, Cursor)\\n   - `HookNames()` - Hook verbs (e.g., [\\\"stop\\\", \\\"user-prompt-submit\\\", \\\"session-start\\\"])\\n   - `ParseHookEvent(ctx, hookName, stdin)` - Translate agent-native hook to normalized Event\\n   - `InstallHooks(ctx, localDev, force)` - Install agent-specific hooks, return count\\n   - `UninstallHooks(ctx)` - Remove installed hooks\\n   - `AreHooksInstalled(ctx)` - Check if hooks currently installed\\n\\n2. **FileWatcher** - For agents without hook support (Aider)\\n   - `GetWatchPaths()` - Paths to watch for session changes\\n   - `OnFileChange(path)` - Handle detected file change, return session info\\n\\n3. **TranscriptAnalyzer** - Format-specific transcript parsing\\n   - `GetTranscriptPosition(path)` - Current position (line count for JSONL, message count for JSON)\\n   - `ExtractModifiedFilesFromOffset(path, offset)` - Files modified since offset\\n   - `ExtractPrompts(sessionRef, fromOffset)` - User prompts from transcript\\n   - `ExtractSummary(sessionRef)` - Session summary from transcript\\n\\n4. **TranscriptPreparer** - Pre-read flush/sync (Claude Code async writes)\\n   - `PrepareTranscript(ctx, sessionRef)` - Ensure transcript ready to read\\n\\n5. **TokenCalculator** - Token usage calculation\\n   - `CalculateTokenUsage(transcriptData, fromOffset)` - Compute token usage from transcript\\n\\n6. **TextGenerator** - Non-interactive text generation (e.g., claude --print)\\n   - `GenerateText(ctx, prompt, model)` - Send prompt to CLI, return response\\n\\n7. **HookResponseWriter** - Structured hook responses\\n   - `WriteHookResponse(message)` - Output message via agent's hook response protocol\\n\\n8. **SubagentAwareExtractor** - Subagent (Task tool) contributions\\n   - `ExtractAllModifiedFiles(transcriptData, offset, subagentsDir)` - Files from main + subagents\\n   - `CalculateTotalTokenUsage(transcriptData, offset, subagentsDir)` - Tokens including subagents\\n\\n### 2. Registry System (`registry.go`)\\n\\n**Factory Pattern:**\\n- `Factory` is a function type: `func() Agent`\\n- `Register(name AgentName, factory Factory)` - Called from `init()` in each agent package\\n- Uses thread-safe map with `sync.RWMutex` for agent registration\\n\\n**Key Registry Functions:**\\n- `Get(name)` - Retrieve agent by name\\n- `List()` - All registered agents in sorted order (deterministic)\\n- `DetectAll(ctx)` - All agents with DetectPresence == true\\n- `Detect(ctx)` - First agent whose DetectPresence == true\\n- `GetByAgentType(agentType)` - Linear search instantiating agents until type match found\\n- `AllProtectedDirs()` - Union of ProtectedDirs from all agents\\n- `Default()` - Default agent (Claude Code)\\n\\n**Registered Agent Constants:**\\n```go\\nAgentNameClaudeCode = \\\"claude-code\\\"\\nAgentNameCursor = \\\"cursor\\\"\\nAgentNameGemini = \\\"gemini\\\"\\nAgentNameOpenCode = \\\"opencode\\\"\\nAgentNameFactoryAIDroid = \\\"factoryai-droid\\\"\\n```\\n\\n### 3. Cursor Agent Implementation\\n\\n**Overview** (`/Users/nodo/work/cli/cmd/entire/cli/agent/cursor/`):\\n\\nThe Cursor agent implements the full `Agent` interface plus `HookSupport` and `TranscriptAnalyzer` optional interfaces.\\n\\n**Core Agent Methods** (`cursor.go`):\\n- Self-registers in `init()` via `agent.Register(agent.AgentNameCursor, NewCursorAgent)`\\n- Name: `\\\"cursor\\\"`, Type: `\\\"Cursor\\\"`, Description: `\\\"Cursor - AI-powered code editor\\\"`\\n- IsPreview: `true`\\n- DetectPresence: Checks for `.cursor/` directory in worktree root\\n- ProtectedDirs: `[\\\".cursor\\\"]`\\n\\n**Session Storage:**\\n- GetSessionDir: `~/.cursor/projects/<sanitized-repo-path>/agent-transcripts` (or override via `ENTIRE_TEST_CURSOR_PROJECT_DIR`)\\n- ResolveSessionFile: Handles both IDE nested layout (`<dir>/<id>/<id>.jsonl`) and CLI flat layout (`<dir>/<id>.jsonl`)\\n  - Prefers nested if file or directory exists (IDE creates dir before flushing file)\\n  - Falls back to flat layout\\n- Path sanitization: Strip leading `/`, replace non-alphanumeric with `-`\\n- ReadSession: Reads JSONL transcript, returns AgentSession with NativeData (ModifiedFiles empty - relies on git status)\\n- WriteSession: Writes session NativeData back to transcript file\\n- FormatResumeCommand: Returns \\\"Open this project in Cursor to continue the session.\\\" (GUI IDE, no CLI resume)\\n\\n**Hook Support** (`hooks.go`):\\n- HookNames: `[\\\"session-start\\\", \\\"session-end\\\", \\\"before-submit-prompt\\\", \\\"stop\\\", \\\"pre-compact\\\", \\\"subagent-start\\\", \\\"subagent-stop\\\"]`\\n- Hook config file: `.cursor/hooks.json` (project-local) with JSON structure:\\n  ```json\\n  {\\n    \\\"version\\\": 1,\\n    \\\"hooks\\\": {\\n      \\\"sessionStart\\\": [{\\\"command\\\": \\\"entire hooks cursor session-start\\\"}],\\n      \\\"sessionEnd\\\": [...],\\n      \\\"beforeSubmitPrompt\\\": [...],\\n      \\\"stop\\\": [...],\\n      \\\"preCompact\\\": [...],\\n      \\\"subagentStart\\\": [...],\\n      \\\"subagentStop\\\": [...]\\n    }\\n  }\\n  ```\\n- InstallHooks: Adds entire hook commands, preserves unknown fields via `map[string]json.RawMessage`\\n  - Command format: `\\\"entire hooks cursor <hook-name>\\\"` or `\\\"go run ${CURSOR_PROJECT_DIR}/cmd/entire/main.go hooks cursor <hook-name>\\\"` (localDev)\\n  - Returns count of hooks installed\\n  - Force flag removes existing Entire hooks before installing\\n- UninstallHooks: Removes all Entire hooks, preserves other user hooks\\n- AreHooksInstalled: Checks if any Entire hook exists in any hook type\\n\\n**Hook Event Parsing** (`lifecycle.go`):\\n- ParseHookEvent dispatches to specific parsers based on hookName\\n  - `session-start` → SessionStart event\\n  - `before-submit-prompt` → TurnStart event (with user prompt)\\n  - `stop` → TurnEnd event\\n  - `session-end` → SessionEnd event\\n  - `pre-compact` → Compaction event\\n  - `subagent-start` → SubagentStart event (with subagentID, type, task description)\\n  - `subagent-stop` → SubagentEnd event (with subagentID, type, task description)\\n\\n- Hook input structures (all JSON via stdin):\\n  - Common fields: conversation_id, generation_id, model, hook_event_name, cursor_version, workspace_roots, user_email, transcript_path\\n  - sessionStart: is_background_agent, composer_mode (IDE only)\\n  - stop: status, loop_count\\n  - sessionEnd: reason, duration_ms, is_background_agent, final_status\\n  - beforeSubmitPrompt: prompt\\n  - preCompact: trigger, context_usage_percent, context_tokens, context_window_size, message_count, messages_to_compact, is_first_compaction\\n  - subagentStart: subagent_id, subagent_type, subagent_model, task, parent_conversation_id, tool_call_id, is_parallel_worker\\n  - subagentStop: subagent_id, subagent_type, status, duration_ms, summary, parent_conversation_id, message_count, tool_call_count, modified_files, loop_count, task, description, agent_transcript_path\\n\\n- **Critical feature:** `resolveTranscriptRef()` - When transcript_path is null (CLI mode), computes path dynamically from repo root using GetSessionDir + ResolveSessionFile\\n- ReadTranscript: Reads JSONL bytes from sessionRef (file path)\\n\\n**Transcript Analysis** (`transcript.go`):\\n- Implements TranscriptAnalyzer interface\\n- GetTranscriptPosition: Counts lines in JSONL file using bufio.Reader (handles arbitrarily long lines)\\n- ExtractPrompts: Parses JSONL using shared `transcript` package (normalizes \\\"role\\\" → \\\"type\\\", strips IDE context tags)\\n- ExtractSummary: Walks backward to find last assistant message text block\\n- Extract