internals that change\\n\\n2. **TestAgentPackages_SelfRegister** - Verifies each agent package has `init()` calling `Register()`:\\n   - Ensures agents are discoverable via registry\\n   - Checks all Go files in agent subdirectories (except types, testutil)\\n\\n### 6. Hook Integration (`hooks_cmd.go`)\\n\\nLocation: `/Users/nodo/work/cli/cmd/entire/cli/hooks_cmd.go`\\n\\nThe hooks command dynamically builds agent hook subcommands:\\n```go\\n// Blank imports ensure agents are registered before iteration\\n_ \\\"github.com/entireio/cli/cmd/entire/cli/agent/claudecode\\\"\\n_ \\\"github.com/entireio/cli/cmd/entire/cli/agent/cursor\\\"\\n_ \\\"github.com/entireio/cli/cmd/entire/cli/agent/factoryaidroid\\\"\\n_ \\\"github.com/entireio/cli/cmd/entire/cli/agent/geminicli\\\"\\n_ \\\"github.com/entireio/cli/cmd/entire/cli/agent/opencode\\\"\\n\\n// In newHooksCmd():\\nfor _, agentName := range agent.List() {\\n    ag, err := agent.Get(agentName)\\n    if err != nil {\\n        continue\\n    }\\n    if handler, ok := ag.(agent.HookSupport); ok {\\n        cmd.AddCommand(newAgentHooksCmd(agentName, handler))\\n    }\\n}\\n```\\n\\nThis creates subcommand trees like `entire hooks cursor <hook-name>`.\\n\\n### 7. Cursor-Specific Documentation\\n\\n**AGENT.md** (`/Users/nodo/work/cli/cmd/entire/cli/agent/cursor/AGENT.md`):\\n\\n**Verdict:** COMPATIBLE\\n\\n**Key Differences from IDE:**\\n- In `-p` (headless) mode: Only `sessionStart`, `sessionEnd`, `preToolUse`, `postToolUse` fire\\n- `beforeSubmitPrompt` and `stop` do NOT fire in headless mode\\n- `transcript_path` is always `null` in CLI mode (existing code handles via `resolveTranscriptRef()`)\\n\\n**Session Location:**\\n- `~/.cursor/projects/<sanitized-repo-path>/agent-transcripts/<conversation-id>.jsonl`\\n- IDE uses nested: `<dir>/<id>/<id>.jsonl`\\n- CLI uses flat: `<dir>/<id>.jsonl`\\n\\n**Binary Info:**\\n- Name: `agent`\\n- Version: `2026.02.13-41ac335`\\n- Install: `curl -fsSL https://cursor.com/install-agent | bas