\"cwd\":\"/Users/nodo/work/cli\",\"sessionId\":\"b12319af-9a0a-4691-b084-e5fc5ae7e446\",\"version\":\"2.1.66\",\"gitBranch\":\"nodo/external-plugins\",\"slug\":\"elegant-singing-yao\",\"type\":\"user\",\"message\":{\"role\":\"user\",\"content\":[{\"tool_use_id\":\"toolu_01TZHaKSeZmoXXvAr3egLqV7\",\"type\":\"tool_result\",\"content\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"Now I have a complete picture. Let me provide a comprehensive report of everything recovered.\\n\\n---\\n\\nHere is the full content of all recovered cursor agent files and the supporting context you need.\\n\\n---\\n\\n## Recovered Cursor Agent Files\\n\\nAll files are recoverable from commit `366e4eeb` (the last commit before deletion in `0041c8e6`).\\n\\n---\\n\\n### `/cmd/entire/cli/agent/cursor/cursor.go`\\n\\nThe main agent struct implementing `agent.Agent`.\\n\\n**Key imports:**\\n- `github.com/entireio/cli/cmd/entire/cli/agent`\\n- `github.com/entireio/cli/cmd/entire/cli/agent/types`\\n- `github.com/entireio/cli/cmd/entire/cli/paths`\\n\\n**Methods:**\\n\\n- `init()` - Self-registers via `agent.Register(agent.AgentNameCursor, NewCursorAgent)`\\n- `Name()` → `agent.AgentNameCursor` (\\\"cursor\\\")\\n- `Type()` → `agent.AgentTypeCursor` (\\\"Cursor\\\")\\n- `Description()` → \\\"Cursor - AI-powered code editor\\\"\\n- `IsPreview()` → `true`\\n- `DetectPresence(ctx)` → checks if `.cursor/` dir exists at worktree root\\n- `GetSessionID(input)` → returns `input.SessionID`\\n- `ResolveSessionFile(sessionDir, agentSessionID)` → handles both IDE nested layout (`<dir>/<id>/<id>.jsonl`) and CLI flat layout (`<dir>/<id>.jsonl`), preferring nested if directory exists\\n- `ProtectedDirs()` → `[]string{\\\".cursor\\\"}`\\n- `GetSessionDir(repoPath)` → `~/.cursor/projects/<sanitized-path>/agent-transcripts`; env override: `ENTIRE_TEST_CURSOR_PROJECT_DIR`\\n- `ReadSession(input)` → reads raw JSONL bytes from `input.SessionRef`; ModifiedFiles left empty (git status used instead)\\n- `WriteSession(ctx, session)` → writes `session.NativeData` to `session.SessionRef`\\n- `FormatResumeCommand(sessionID)` → returns \\\"Open this project in Cursor to continue the session.\\\"\\n- `sanitizePathForCursor(path)` → strips leading `/`, replaces all non-alphanumeric with `-`\\n- `ChunkTranscript(ctx, content, maxSize)` → delegates to `agent.ChunkJSONL`\\n- `ReassembleTranscript(chunks)` → delegates to `agent.ReassembleJSONL`\\n\\n---\\n\\n### `/cmd/entire/cli/agent/cursor/hooks.go`\\n\\nImplements `agent.HookSupport` interface.\\n\\n**Key imports:**\\n- `github.com/entireio/cli/cmd/entire/cli/agent`\\n- `github.com/entireio/cli/cmd/entire/cli/jsonutil`\\n- `github.com/entireio/cli/cmd/entire/cli/paths`\\n\\n**Hook name constants:**\\n```go\\nHookNameSessionStart       = \\\"session-start\\\"\\nHookNameSessionEnd         = \\\"session-end\\\"\\nHookNameBeforeSubmitPrompt = \\\"before-submit-prompt\\\"\\nHookNameStop               = \\\"stop\\\"\\nHookNamePreCompact         = \\\"pre-compact\\\"\\nHookNameSubagentStart      = \\\"subagent-start\\\"\\nHookNameSubagentStop       = \\\"subagent-stop\\\"\\nHooksFileName              = \\\"hooks.json\\\"\\n```\\n\\n**Hook command prefixes recognized as Entire hooks:**\\n```go\\nvar entireHookPrefixes = []string{\\n    \\\"entire \\\",\\n    \\\"go run ${CURSOR_PROJECT_DIR}/cmd/entire/main.go \\\",\\n}\\n```\\n\\n**Methods:**\\n- `HookNames()` → returns all 7 hook name constants\\n- `InstallHooks(ctx, localDev, force)` → reads/writes `.cursor/hooks.json` using `map[string]json.RawMessage` to preserve unknown fields; local-dev prefix is `go run ${CURSOR_PROJECT_DIR}/cmd/entire/main.go hooks cursor`, prod prefix is `entire hooks cursor`\\n- `UninstallHooks(ctx)` → removes Entire hooks from all 7 hook types in `.cursor/hooks.json`\\n- `AreHooksInstalled(ctx)` → checks for any Entire hook in `.cursor/hooks.json`\\n- `GetSupportedHooks()` → returns `[]agent.HookType{HookSessionStart, HookSessionEnd, HookUserPromptSubmit, HookStop, HookPreToolUse, HookPostToolUse}`\\n\\n**Internal helpers:**\\n- `parseCursorHookType(rawHooks, hookType, target)` - unmarshals a hook type from raw map\\n- `marshalCursorHookType(rawHooks, hookType, entries)` - marshals back; deletes key if empty\\n- `hookCommandExists(entries, command)` - deduplication check\\n- `isEntireHook(command)` - checks against `entireHookPrefixes`\\n- `hasEntireHook(entries)` - checks slice\\n- `removeEntireHooks(entries)` - filters out Entire hooks\\n\\n---\\n\\n### `/cmd/entire/cli/agent/cursor/lifecycle.go`\\n\\nImplements `ParseHookEvent` and transcript reading.\\n\\n**Key imports:**\\n- `github.com/entireio/cli/cmd/entire/cli/agent`\\n- `github.com/entireio/cli/cmd/entire/cli/logging`\\n- `github.com/entireio/cli/cmd/entire/cli/paths`\\n\\n**Methods:**\\n- `ParseHookEvent(ctx, hookName, stdin)` → dispatches to one of the 7 parse functions below\\n- `ReadTranscript(sessionRef)` → reads raw bytes from file\\n- `resolveTranscriptRef(ctx, conversationID, rawPath)` → returns rawPath if non-empty, otherwise dynamically computes path via `paths.WorktreeRoot` + `GetSessionDir` + `ResolveSessionFile` (handles CLI mode where `transcript_path` is always `null`)\\n\\n**Hook parsers (private):**\\n- `parseSessionStart(stdin)` → reads `sessionStartRaw`, returns `Event{Type: SessionStart, SessionID: raw.ConversationID, SessionRef: raw.TranscriptPath}`\\n- `parseTurnStart(ctx, stdin)` → reads `beforeSubmitPromptInputRaw`, returns `Event{Type: TurnStart, ..., Prompt: raw.Prompt, Model: raw.Model}`\\n- `parseTurnEnd(ctx, stdin)` → reads `stopHookInputRaw`, returns `Event{Type: TurnEnd, ..., Model: raw.Model}`\\n- `parseSessionEnd(ctx, stdin)` → reads `sessionEndRaw`, returns `Event{Type: SessionEnd}`\\n- `parsePreCompact(stdin)` → reads `preCompactHookInputRaw`, returns `Event{Type: Compaction}`\\n- `parseSubagentStart(stdin)` → reads `subagentStartHookInputRaw`; returns `nil` if `raw.Task == \\\"\\\"`; otherwise `Event{Type: SubagentStart, SubagentID: raw.SubagentID, ToolUseID: raw.SubagentID, SubagentType: raw.SubagentType, TaskDescription: raw.Task}`\\n- `parseSubagentStop(stdin)` → reads `subagentStopHookInputRaw`; returns `nil` if `raw.Task == \\\"\\\"`; otherwise `Event{Type: SubagentEnd, ToolUseID: raw.SubagentID, ModifiedFiles: raw.ModifiedFiles}`\\n\\n---\\n\\n### `/cmd/entire/cli/agent/cursor/transcript.go`\\n\\nImplements `agent.TranscriptAnalyzer`.\\n\\n**Key imports:**\\n- `github.com/entireio/cli/cmd/entire/cli/agent`\\n- `github.com/entireio/cli/cmd/entire/cli/textutil`\\n- `github.com/entireio/cli/cmd/entire/cli/transcript`\\n\\n**Methods:**\\n- `GetTranscriptPosition(path)` → counts lines using `bufio.NewReader` (handles arbitrarily long lines); returns 0 if file doesn't exist\\n- `ExtractPrompts(sessionRef, fromOffset)` → uses `transcript.ParseFromFileAtLine(sessionRef, fromOffset)`, filters for `TypeUser`, calls `transcript.ExtractUserContent`, then `textutil.StripIDEContextTags`\\n- `ExtractSummary(sessionRef)` → reads all bytes, parses with `transcript.ParseFromBytes`, walks backward to find last assistant block of `ContentTypeText`\\n- `ExtractModifiedFilesFromOffset(path, offset)` → always returns `nil, 0, nil` because Cursor transcripts don't contain tool_use blocks; file detection relies on git status and hook-provided `modified_files`\\n\\n---\\n\\n### `/cmd/entire/cli/agent/cursor/types.go`\\n\\nAll type definitions.\\n\\n**Struct types:**\\n- `CursorHooksFile` - top-level `.cursor/hooks.json` structure (`Version int`, `Hooks CursorHooks`)\\n- `CursorHooks` - hook type groups (7 fields: `SessionStart`, `SessionEnd`, `BeforeSubmitPrompt`, `Stop`, `PreCompact`, `SubagentStart`, `SubagentStop`, each `[]CursorHookEntry`)\\n- `CursorHookEntry` - single hook entry (`Command string`, `Matcher string,omitempty`)\\n\\n**Raw input structs** (all share common fields `ConversationID`, `GenerationID`, `Model`, `HookEventName`, `CursorVersion`, `WorkspaceRoots`, `UserEmail`, `TranscriptPath`):\\n- `sessionStartRaw` - adds `IsBackgroundAgent bool`, `ComposerMode string` (IDE-only)\\n- `stopHookInputRaw` - adds `Status string`, `LoopCount json.Number`\\n- `sessionEndRaw` - adds `Reason string`, `DurationMs json.Number`, `IsBackgroundAgent bool`, `FinalStatus string`\\n- `beforeSubmitPromptInputRaw` - adds `Prompt string`\\n- `preCompactHookInputRaw` - adds `Trigger`, `ContextUsagePercent`, `ContextTokens`, `ContextWindowSize`, `MessageCount`, `MessagesToCompact json.Number`, `IsFirstCompaction bool`\\n- `subagentStartHookInputRaw` - adds `SubagentID`, `SubagentType`, `SubagentModel`, `Task`, `ParentConversationID`, `ToolCallID string`, `IsParallelWorker bool`\\n- `subagentStopHookInputRaw` - adds `SubagentID`, `SubagentType`, `Status`, `Duration`, `Summary`, `ParentConversationID`, `MessageCount`, `ToolCallCount`, `ModifiedFiles []string`, `LoopCount`, `Task`, `Description`, `AgentTranscriptPath`\\n\\n---\\n\\n## External Agent Protocol — How Cursor Methods Map to Subcommands\\n\\nThe cursor code was deleted because it is being migrated to the external agent binary protocol. Here is the complete mapping:\\n\\n| Cursor method | External binary subcommand |\\n|---|---|\\n| `Name/Type/Description/IsPreview/ProtectedDirs/HookNames` | `info` (static in JSON response) |\\n| `DetectPresence(ctx)` | `detect` → `{\\\"present\\\": bool}` |\\n| `GetSessionID(input)` | `get-session-id` (stdin: HookInputJSON) |\\n| `GetSessionDir(repoPath)` | `get-session-dir --repo-path <path>` |\\n| `ResolveSessionFile(dir, id)` | `resolve-session-file --session-dir <dir> --session-id <id>` |\\n| `ReadSession(input)` | `read-session` (stdin: HookInputJSON) |\\n| `WriteSession(ctx, session)` | `write-session` (stdin: AgentSessionJSON) |\\n| `FormatResumeCommand(id)` | `format-resume-command --session-id <id>` |\\n| `ReadTranscript(ref)` | `read-transcript --session-ref <ref>` |\\n| `ChunkTranscript(ctx, data, max)` | `chunk-transcript --max-size <n>` (stdin: raw bytes) |\\n| `ReassembleTranscript(chunks)` | `