t hook dispatch works end-to-end with external agent\\n- Test that removing built-in Cursor doesn't break any existing tests (the constants remain)\\n\\n### Test commands\\n```bash\\nmise run fmt && mise run lint && mise run test:ci\\n```\\n\\n## Files to Create\\n- `docs/architecture/external-agent-protocol.md` — Protocol specification\\n- `cmd/entire/cli/agent/external/external.go` — Core adapter\\n- `cmd/entire/cli/agent/external/capabilities.go` — Optional interface wrappers\\n- `cmd/entire/cli/agent/external/types.go` — Protocol JSON types\\n- `cmd/entire/cli/agent/external/external_test.go` — Tests\\n\\n## Files to Modify\\n- `cmd/entire/cli/agent/registry.go` — Add `DiscoverExternal()`\\n- `cmd/entire/cli/hooks_cmd.go` — Call discovery, remove cursor import\\n- `cmd/entire/cli/strategy/manual_commit_condensation_test.go` — Remove cursor import\\n- `cmd/entire/cli/agent/architecture_test.go` — Update import validation\\n\\n## Files to Delete\\n- `cmd/entire/cli/agent/cursor/cursor.go`\\n- `cmd/entire/cli/agent/cursor/cursor_test.go`\\n- `cmd/entire/cli/agent/cursor/hooks.go`\\n- `cmd/entire/cli/agent/cursor/hooks_test.go`\\n- `cmd/entire/cli/agent/cursor/lifecycle.go`\\n- `cmd/entire/cli/agent/cursor/lifecycle_test.go`\\n- `cmd/entire/cli/agent/cursor/transcript.go`\\n- `cmd/entire/cli/agent/cursor/transcript_test.go`\\n- `cmd/entire/cli/agent/cursor/types.go`\\n- `cmd/entire/cli/agent/cursor/AGENT.md`\\n\\n## Verification\\n\\n1. `mise run fmt && mise run lint && mise run test:ci` — All pass\\n2. Create a test `entire-agent-test` shell script implementing `info` and `detect`, verify discovery works\\n3. Verify `entire hooks` command tree still builds correctly\\n4. Verify agent type switch statements (`explain.go`, `summarize.go`) still work via the constants\\n\\n## Out of Scope (Follow-up)\\n- **`entire-agent-cursor` binary** — Built in a separate repo, implements the protocol using the extracted Cursor logic\\n- **Migrating other agents** (Gemini, OpenCode, Factory AI Droid) to external binaries\\n- **Batch subcommand** — Optimizing warm-path (turn-end) by combining multiple operations into one exec\\n- **Long-running daemon mode** — Future protocol extension for latency-sensitive scenarios\",\"newString\":\"# Plan: Implement Cursor Agent as External Binary\\n\\n## Context\\n\\nThe external agent protocol and adapter are already implemented (Steps 1-4 from the previous plan are complete). The built-in `cmd/entire/cli/agent/cursor/` package has been deleted. Now we need to implement the cursor agent as an external binary (`entire-agent-cursor`) that implements the external agent protocol, keeping it in this repo for now.\\n\\nThe binary will be at `cmd/entire-agent-cursor/main.go` — a standalone Go binary that can be discovered via `$PATH` by the CLI's `external.DiscoverAndRegister()`.\\n\\n## Step 1: Create the Binary Entry Point\\n\\n**File:** `cmd/entire-agent-cursor/main.go`\\n\\nA simple `main()` that dispatches subcommands. Since this is a protocol binary (not a user CLI), use a switch on `os.Args[1]` rather than cobra. Parse flags with `flag.NewFlagSet` per subcommand.\\n\\nSubcommands to implement (matching the protocol spec):\\n- `info` — static JSON response\\n- `detect` — check `.cursor/` exists\\n- `get-session-id` — extract from stdin HookInput\\n- `get-session-dir` — compute `~/.cursor/projects/<sanitized>/agent-transcripts`\\n- `resolve-session-file` — handle nested vs flat layout\\n- `read-session` — read JSONL from session ref\\n- `write-session` — write native data to session ref\\n- `format-resume-command` — static message\\n- `read-transcript` — read raw bytes\\n- `chunk-transcript` — JSONL line-based chunking (reuse `agent.ChunkJSONL`)\\n- `reassemble-transcript` — JSONL reassembly (reuse `agent.ReassembleJSONL`)\\n- `parse-hook` — dispatch to 7 hook parsers\\n- `install-hooks` — write `.cursor/hooks.json`\\n- `uninstall-hooks` — remove Entire hooks from `.cursor/hooks.json`\\n- `are-hooks-installed` — check `.cursor/hooks.json`\\n- `get-transcript-position` — count JSONL lines\\n- `extract-modified-files` — always returns empty (cursor has no tool_use blocks)\\n- `extract-prompts` — parse JSONL, filter user messages, strip IDE tags\\n- `extract-summary` — find last assistant text block\\n\\n## Step 2: Package Structure\\n\\nSince the binary has significant logic, organize into a package rather than one giant main.go:\\n\\n```\\ncmd/entire-agent-cursor/\\n├── main.go              # Entry point, subcommand dispatch\\n├── cursor.go            # Core logic: detect, session management, path helpers\\n├── hooks.go             # Hook install/uninstall/are-installed logic\\n├── lifecycle.go         # ParseHookEvent: 7 hook parsers\\n├── transcript.go        # TranscriptAnalyzer: position, prompts, summary, modified files\\n└── types.go             # Hook input types, hooks.json types\\n```\\n\\nAll files in `package main`.\\n\\n## Step 3: Reuse Shared Packages\\n\\nThe binary can import shared packages from this repo since it's in the same module:\\n- `github.com/entireio/cli/cmd/entire/cli/agent` — `ChunkJSONL`, `ReassembleJSONL`, `HookInput`, `Event`, `EventType`, `AgentSession`\\n- `github.com/entireio/cli/cmd/entire/cli/transcript` — `ParseFromFileAtLine`, `ParseFromBytes`, `ExtractUserContent`, type constants\\n- `github.com/entireio/cli/cmd/entire/cli/textutil` — `StripIDEContextTags`\\n- `github.com/entireio/cli/cmd/entire/cli/jsonutil` — `MarshalIndentWithNewline`\\n\\n**Key difference from built-in agent:** The binary communicates via JSON stdout, not Go interfaces. Each subcommand reads args/stdin, does the work, and outputs JSON to stdout.\\n\\n## Step 4: Protocol Response Details\\n\\n### `info` response (static):\\n```json\\n{\\n  \\\"protocol_version\\\": 1,\\n  \\\"name\\\": \\\"cursor\\\",\\n  \\\"type\\\": \\\"Cursor\\\",\\n  \\\"description\\\": \\\"Cursor - AI-powered code editor\\\",\\n  \\\"is_preview\\\": true,\\n  \\\"protected_dirs\\\": [\\\".cursor\\\"],\\n  \\\"hook_names\\\": [\\\"session-start\\\",\\\"session-end\\\",\\\"before-submit-prompt\\\",\\\"stop\\\",\\\"pre-compact\\\",\\\"subagent-start\\\",\\\"subagent-stop\\\"],\\n  \\\"capabilities\\\": {\\n    \\\"hooks\\\": true,\\n    \\\"transcript_analyzer\\\": true,\\n    \\\"transcript_preparer\\\": false,\\n    \\\"token_calculator\\\": false,\\n    \\\"text_generator\\\": false,\\n    \\\"hook_response_writer\\\": false,\\n    \\\"subagent_aware_extractor\\\": false\\n  }\\n}\\n```\\n\\n### `parse-hook` response:\\nOutputs the `eventJSON` struct (same format as `external/types.go:eventJSON`). For hooks with no lifecycle significance, outputs `null`.\\n\\n### Session/transcript methods:\\nRead/write files using the same logic as the deleted `cursor.go` — session dir at `~/.cursor/projects/<sanitized-path>/agent-transcripts`, nested vs flat file layout detection.\\n\\n## Step 5: Key Logic to Port\\n\\n### From `cursor.go`:\\n- `sanitizePathForCursor(path)` — strips leading `/`, replaces non-alphanumeric with `-`\\n- `DetectPresence` — check `ENTIRE_REPO_ROOT` env + `.cursor/` dir exists\\n- `GetSessionDir` — `~/.cursor/projects/<sanitized>/agent-transcripts`, with `ENTIRE_TEST_CURSOR_PROJECT_DIR` override\\n- `ResolveSessionFile` — check nested (`dir/id/id.jsonl`) first, fall back to flat (`dir/id.jsonl`)\\n- `ReadSession` — resolve session file, read raw JSONL bytes, return as AgentSession JSON\\n- `WriteSession` — write native data to session ref path\\n\\n### From `hooks.go`:\\n- `InstallHooks` — read/modify `.cursor/hooks.json` using `map[string]json.RawMessage` to preserve unknown fields\\n- `UninstallHooks` — remove Entire hook entries from all 7 hook types\\n- `AreHooksInstalled` — check for any Entire hook command prefix\\n- Recognized prefixes: `\\\"entire \\\"` and `\\\"go run ${CURSOR_PROJECT_DIR}/cmd/entire/main.go \\\"`\\n\\n### From `lifecycle.go`:\\n- `ParseHookEvent` — switch on hook name, dispatch to 7 parsers\\n- Each parser reads stdin JSON, maps to protocol event JSON\\n- `resolveTranscriptRef` — if transcript path is empty, dynamically compute it from env\\n\\n### From `transcript.go`:\\n- `GetTranscriptPosition` — count lines with bufio.Reader\\n- `ExtractPrompts` — use `transcript.ParseFromFileAtLine`, filter TypeUser, extract content, strip IDE tags\\n- `ExtractSummary` — parse all, walk backward for last assistant text block\\n- `ExtractModifiedFilesFromOffset` — always returns `{\\\"files\\\": null, \\\"current_position\\\": 0}`\\n\\n## Step 6: Tests\\n\\n**File:** `cmd/entire-agent-cursor/cursor_test.go` (and per-file tests)\\n\\nTest the binary end-to-end by:\\n1. Building the binary with `go build`\\n2. Running subcommands and checking JSON output\\n3. Testing hook parsing with sample stdin payloads\\n\\nAlso test individual functions unit-style:\\n- `sanitizePathForCursor` — various path inputs\\n- Hook JSON round-trip preservation\\n- Transcript line counting\\n\\n## Files to Create\\n- `cmd/entire-agent-cursor/main.go` — Entry point + subcommand dispatch\\n- `cmd/entire-agent-cursor/cursor.go` — Core: detect, session, path helpers\\n- `cmd/entire-agent-cursor/hooks.go` — Hook install/uninstall\\n- `cmd/entire-agent-cursor/lifecycle.go` — ParseHookEvent dispatching\\n- `cmd/entire-agent-cursor/transcript.go` — Transcript analysis\\n- `cmd/entire-agent-cursor/types.go` — Type definitions\\n- `cmd/entire-agent-cursor/cursor_test.go` — Tests\\n\\n## Files to Modify\\n- None (the external adapter and discovery are already in place)\\n\\n## Verification\\n\\n1. `go build ./cmd/entire-agent-cursor/` — binary compiles\\n2. `./entire-agent-cursor info` — outputs valid info JSON\\n3. `./entire-agent-cursor detect` — checks `.cursor/` presence\\n4. `mise run fmt && mise run lint && mise run test:ci` — all pass\\n5. Place binary on PATH, verify `external.DiscoverAndRegister()` discovers it\\n6. Verify `entire hooks cursor ...` subcommands work end-to-end\",\"originalFile\":\"# Plan: External Agent Plugin Protocol + Cursor Extraction\\n\\n## Context\\n\\nThe CLI currently has all agent implementations compiled in (Claude Code, Cursor, Gemini CLI, OpenCode, Factory AI Droid). To make the CLI extensible — allowing third-party agents without modifying the main repo — we need a protocol for external agent binaries that the CLI discovers via PATH and communicates with over stdin/stdout.\\n\\n**Starting point:** Extract the Cursor agent into a separate repo (`entire-agent-cursor`) as the first external agent. The built-in Cursor code will be removed from this repo.\\n\\n## Step 1: Define the Protocol Specification\\n\\nCreate `docs/architecture/external-agent-protocol.md` documenting the full protocol.\\n\\n**Protocol summary:**\\n- **Discovery:** CLI scans PATH for `entire-agent-<name>` binaries\\n- **Communication:** Subcommand-based, JSON over stdin/stdout, raw bytes for transcripts\\n- **Stateless:** Each invocation is independent\\n- **Environment:** `ENTIRE_REPO_ROOT` and `ENTIRE_PROTOCOL_VERSION=1` are always set; working directory is repo root\\n\\n**Subcommands** (each maps to an Agent interface method):\\n\\n| Subcommand | Required | Maps to | I/O |\\n|---|---|---|---|\\n| `info` | Always | Name/Type/Description/IsPreview/ProtectedDirs/HookNames + capabilities | stdout: JSON |\\n| `detect` | Always | DetectPresence | stdout: `{\\\"present\\\": bool}` |\\n| `parse-hook --hook <name>` | If hooks capable | ParseHookEvent | stdin: raw agent payload → stdout: JSON Event or `null` |\\n| `read-transcript --session-ref <path>` | Always | ReadTranscript | stdout: raw bytes |\\n| `chunk-transcript --max-size <n>` | Always | ChunkTranscript | stdin: raw → stdout: JSON `{\\\"chunks\\\": [\\\"base64...\\\"]}` |\\n| `reassemble-transcript` | Always | ReassembleTranscript | stdin: JSON chunks → stdout: raw |\\n| `get-session-id` | Always | GetSessionID | stdin: JSON HookInput → stdout: `{\\\"session_id\\\": \\\"...\\\"}` |\\n| `get-session-dir --repo-path <p>` | Always | GetSessionDir | stdout: `{\\\"session_dir\\\": \\\"...\\\"}` |\\n| `resolve-session-file --session-dir <d> --session-id <id>` | Always | ResolveSessionFile | stdout: `{\\\"session_file\\\": \\\"...\\\"}` |\\n| `read-session` | Always | ReadSession | stdin: JSON HookInput → stdout: JSON AgentSession |\\n| `write-session` | Always | WriteSession | stdin: JSON AgentSession → exit 0 |\\n| `format-resume-command --session-id <id>` | Always | FormatResumeCommand | stdout: `{\\\"command\\\": \\\"...\\\"}` |\\n| `install-hooks [--local-dev] [--force]` | If hooks | InstallHooks | stdout: `{\\\"hooks_installed\\\": N}` |\\n| `uninstall-hooks` | If hooks | UninstallHooks | exit 0 |\\n| `are-hooks-installed` | If hooks | AreHooksInstalled | stdout: `{\\\"installed\\\": bool}` |\\n| `get-transcript-position --path <p>` | If transcript_analyzer | GetTranscriptPosition | stdout: `{\\\"position\\\": N}` |\\n| `extract-modified-files --path <p> --offset <n>` | If transcript_analyzer | ExtractModifiedFilesFromOffset | stdout: JSON |\\n| `extract-prompts --session-ref <p> --offset <n>` | If transcript_analyzer | ExtractPrompts | stdout: JSON |\\n| `extract-summary --session-ref <p>` | If transcript_analyzer | ExtractSummary | stdout: JSON |\\n| `prepare-transcript --session-ref <p>` | If transcript_preparer | PrepareTranscript | exit 0 |\\n| `calculate-tokens --offset <n>` | If token_calculator | CalculateTokenUsage | stdin: raw → stdout: JSON |\\n| `generate-text --model <m>` | If text_generator | GenerateText | stdin: prompt → stdout: JSON |\\n| `write-hook-response --message <m>` | If hook_response_writer | WriteHookResponse | stdout: agent-native format |\\n| `extract-all-modified-files --offset <n> --subagents-dir <d>` | If subagent_aware | ExtractAllModifiedFiles | stdin: raw → stdout: JSON |\\n| `calculate-total-tokens --offset <n> --subagents-dir <d>` | If subagent_aware | CalculateTotalTokenUsage | stdin: raw → stdout: JSON |\\n\\n**`info` response** declares capabilities:\\n```json\\n{\\n  \\\"protocol_version\\\": 1,\\n  \\\"name\\\": \\\"cursor\\\",\\n  \\\"type\\\": \\\"Cursor\\\",\\n  \\\"description\\\": \\\"Cursor - AI-powered code editor\\\",\\n  \\\"is_preview\\\": true,\\n  \\\"protected_dirs\\\": [\\\".cursor\\\"],\\n  \\\"hook_names\\\": [\\\"session-start\\\", \\\"session-end\\\", \\\"stop\\\", ...],\\n  \\\"capabilities\\\": {\\n    \\\"hooks\\\": true,\\n    \\\"transcript_analyzer\\\": true,\\n    \\\"transcript_preparer\\\": false,\\n    \\\"token_calculator\\\": false,\\n    \\\"text_generator\\\": false,\\n    \\\"hook_response_writer\\\": false,\\n    \\\"subagent_aware_extractor\\\": false\\n  }\\n}\\n```\\n\\n**Error handling:** exit 0 = success, non-zero = error with message on stderr.\\n\\n## Step 2: Create ExternalAgent Adapter\\n\\nCreate `cmd/entire/cli/agent/external/` package with:\\n\\n### `external.go` — Core adapter\\n\\n```go\\ntype ExternalAgent struct {\\n    binaryPath string\\n    info       *InfoResponse  // cached from `info`\\n}\\n```\\n\\n- Implements `agent.Agent` (all 14 methods) by shelling out to the binary\\n- Each method: build args → exec binary → parse JSON response\\n- Helper: `exec(ctx, subcommand, args, stdin) (stdout, error)`\\n\\n### `capabilities.go` — Optional interface wrappers\\n\\nSince Go interfaces are checked at compile time via type assertions, the adapter needs wrapper types for each optional interface:\\n\\n```go\\n// ExternalAgentWithHooks wraps ExternalAgent and implements agent.HookSupport\\ntype ExternalAgentWithHooks struct{ *ExternalAgent }\\n\\n// ExternalAgentWithAnalyzer wraps ExternalAgent and implements agent.TranscriptAnalyzer\\ntype ExternalAgentWithAnalyzer struct{ *ExternalAgent }\\n\\n// ... etc for each optional interface\\n```\\n\\nA `NewExternalAgent(binaryPath)` constructor calls `info`, caches the response, and returns the appropriate wrapper combining all declared capabilities. Uses Go embedding + interface composition.\\n\\n### `types.go` — Protocol JSON types\\n\\nJSON request/response structs for all subcommands (InfoResponse, EventResponse, SessionResponse, etc.).\\n\\n### `external_test.go` — Unit tests\\n\\nTest the adapter with a mock binary (shell script or test helper that implements the protocol).\\n\\n**Key files:**\\n- `cmd/entire/cli/agent/external/external.go`\\n- `cmd/entire/cli/agent/external/capabilities.go`\\n- `cmd/entire/cli/agent/external/types.go`\\n- `cmd/entire/cli/agent/external/external_test.go`\\n\\n## Step 3: Add PATH Discovery to Registry\\n\\nModify `cmd/entire/cli/agent/registry.go`:\\n\\n- Add `DiscoverExternal()` function that:\\n  1. Scans `$PATH` for executables matching `entire-agent-*`\\n  2. For each found binary, calls `entire-agent-<name> info`\\n  3. Creates an `ExternalAgent` adapter\\n  4. Registers it via `Register(name, factory)`\\n- Skip binaries whose name conflicts with already-registered (built-in) agents\\n\\nModify `cmd/entire/cli/hooks_cmd.go`:\\n\\n- Call `DiscoverExternal()` before building the hooks command tree (alongside the blank imports)\\n- Remove the `_ \\\"github.com/entireio/cli/cmd/entire/cli/agent/cursor\\\"` blank import\\n\\n## Step 4: Remove Built-in Cursor Agent\\n\\nDelete `cmd/entire/cli/agent/cursor/` directory entirely (9 files).\\n\\n**Keep in this repo** (not Cursor-specific):\\n- `AgentNameCursor` / `AgentTypeCursor` constants in `registry.go` — used in switch statements in `explain.go`, `summarize.go`, `manual_commit_condensation.go`\\n- `transcript` package — shared JSONL parsing (handles role→type normalization)\\n- `textutil` package — IDE tag stripping (handles `<user_query>` tags)\\n\\n**Update references:**\\n- `hooks_cmd.go`: Remove cursor blank import\\n- `strategy/manual_commit_condensation_test.go`: Remove cursor blank import, adjust test to use external agent or mock\\n- `agent/architecture_test.go`: Update if it validates cursor package imports\\n\\n## Step 5: Tests\\n\\n### Unit tests for ExternalAgent adapter\\n- Mock binary (test helper script) implementing the protocol\\n- Test each method delegation\\n- Test capability-based interface composition\\n- Test error handling (binary not found, non-zero exit, malformed JSON)\\n\\n### Integration tests\\n- Test PATH discovery finds and registers external agents\\n- Test hook dispatch works end-to-end with external agent\\n- Test that removing built-in Cursor doesn't break any existing tests (the constants remain)\\n\\n### Test commands\\n```bash\\nmise run fmt && mise run lint && mise run test:ci\\n```\\n\\n## Files to Create\\n- `docs/architecture/external-agent-protocol.md` — Protocol specification\\n- `cmd/entire/cli/agent/external/external.go` — Core adapter\\n- `cmd/entire/cli/agent/external/capabilities.go` — Optional interface wrappers\\n- `cmd/entire/cli/agent/external/types.go` — Protocol JSON types\\n- `cmd/entire/cli/agent/external/external_test.go` — Tests\\n\\n## Files to Modify\\n- `cmd/entire/cli/agent/registry.go` — Add `DiscoverExternal()`\\n- `cmd/entire/cli/hooks_cmd.go` — Call discovery, remove cursor import\\n- `cmd/entire/cli/strategy/manual_commit_condensation_test.go` — Remove cursor import\\n- `cmd/entire/cli/agent/architecture_test.go` — Update import validation\\n\\n## Files to Delete\\n- `cmd/entire/cli/agent/cursor/cursor.go`\\n- `cmd/entire/cli/agent/cursor/cursor_test.go`\\n- `cmd/entire/cli/agent/cursor/hooks.go`\\n- `cmd/entire/cli/agent/cursor/hooks_test.go`\\n- `cmd/entire/cli/agent/cursor/lifecycle.go`\\n- `cmd/entire/cli/agent/cursor/lifecycle_test.go`\\n- `cmd/entire/cli/agent/cursor/transcript.go`\\n- `cmd/entire/cli/agent/cursor/transcript_test.go`\\n- `cmd/entire/cli/agent/cursor/types.go`\\n- `cmd/entire/cli/agent/cursor/AGENT.md`\\n\\n## Verification\\n\\n1. `mise run fmt && mise run lint && mise run test:ci` — All pass\\n2. Create a test `entire-agent-test` shell script implementing `info` and `detect`, verify discovery works\\n3. Verify `entire hooks` command tree still builds correctly\\n4. Verify agent type switch statements (`explain.go`, `summarize.go`) still work via the constants\\n\\n## Out of Scope (Follow-up)\\n- **`entire-agent-cursor` binary** — Built in a separate repo, implements the protocol using the extracted Cursor logic\\n- **Migrating other agents** (Gemini, OpenCode, Factory AI Droid) to external binaries\\n- **Batch subcommand** — Optimizing warm-path (turn-end) by combining multiple operations into one exec\\n- **Long-running daemon mode** — Future protocol extension for latency-sensitive scenarios\\n\",\"structuredPatch\":[{\"oldStart\":1,\"oldLines\":52,\"newStart\":1,\"newLines\":67,\"lines\":[\"-# Plan: External Agent Plugin Protocol + Cursor Extraction\",\"+# Plan: Implement Cursor Agent as External Binary\",\" \",\" ## Context\",\" \",\"-The CLI currently has all agent implementations compiled in (Claude Code, Cursor, Gemini CLI, OpenCode, Factory AI Droid). To make the CLI extensible — allowing third-party agents without modifying the main repo — we need a protocol for external agent binaries that the CLI discovers via PATH and communicates with over stdin/stdout.\",\"+The external agent protocol and adapter are already implemented (Steps 1-4 from the previous plan are complete). The built-in `cmd/entire/cli/agent/cursor/` package has been deleted. Now we need to implement the cursor agent as an external binary (`entire-agent-cursor`) that implements the external agent protocol, keeping it in this repo for now.\",\" \",\"-**Starting point:** Extract the Cursor agent into a separate repo (`entire-agent-cursor`) as the first external agent. The built-in Cursor code will be removed from this repo.\",\"+The binary will be at `cmd/entire-agent-cursor/main.go` — a standalone Go binary that can be discovered via `$PATH` by the CLI's `external.DiscoverAndRegister()`.\",\" \",\"-## Step 1: Define the Protocol Specification\",\"+## Step 1: Create the Binary Entry Point\",\" \",\"-Create `docs/architecture/external-agent-protocol.md` documenting the full protocol.\",\"+**File:** `cmd/entire-agent-cursor/main.go`\",\" \",\"-**Protocol summary:**\",\"-- **Discovery:** CLI scans PATH for `entire-agent-<name>` binaries\",\"-- **Communication:** Subcommand-based, JSON over stdin/stdout, raw bytes for transcripts\",\"-- **Stateless:** Each invocation is independent\",\"-- **Environment:** `ENTIRE_REPO_ROOT` and `ENTIRE_PROTOCOL_VERSION=1` are always set; working directory is repo root\",\"+A simple `main()` that dispatches subcommands. Since this is a protocol binary (not a user CLI), use a switch on `os.Args[1]` rather than cobra. Parse flags with `flag.NewFlagSet` per subcommand.\",\" \",\"-**Subcommands** (each maps to an Agent interface method):\",\"+Subcommands to implement (matching the protocol spec):\",\"+- `info` — static JSON response\",\"+- `detect` — check `.cursor/` exists\",\"+- `get-session-id` — extract from stdin HookInput\",\"+- `get-session-dir` — compute `~/.cursor/projects/<sanitized>/agent-transcripts`\",\"+- `resolve-session-file` — handle nested vs flat layout\",\"+- `read-session` — read JSONL from session ref\",\"+- `write-session` — write native data to session ref\",\"+- `format-resume-command` — static message\",\"+- `read-transcript` — read raw bytes\",\"+- `chunk-transcript` — JSONL line-based chunking (reuse `agent.ChunkJSONL`)\",\"+- `reassemble-transcript` — JSONL reassembly (reuse `agent.ReassembleJSONL`)\",\"+- `parse-hook` — dispatch to 7 hook parsers\",\"+- `install-hooks` — write `.cursor/hooks.json`\",\"+- `uninstall-hooks` — remove Entire hooks from `.cursor/hooks.json`\",\"+- `are-hooks-installed` — check `.cursor/hooks.json`\",\"+- `get-transcript-position` — count JSONL lines\",\"+- `extract-modified-files` — always returns empty (cursor has no tool_use blocks)\",\"+- `extract-prompts` — parse JSONL, filter user messages, strip IDE tags\",\"+- `extract-summary` — find last assistant text block\",\" \",\"-| Subcommand | Required | Maps to | I/O |\"